event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"\n\n## OpenAgentic Platform Health Score\n\n# 38 / 100\n\nThe platform is **operationally functional for basic chat** but its knowledge layer, observability stack, and rate limiting are all broken. Users can send messages and get LLM responses, but every RAG-enhanced feature is silently failing.\n\n---\n\n### Score Breakdown\n\n| Domain | Weight | Score | Weighted | Rationale |\n|--------|:------:|:-----:|:--------:|-----------|\n| **Core Orchestration** (LangGraph, CrewAI) | 20% | 90 | 18.0 | Both healthy; Flowise unhealthy but not default |\n| **Vector DB / Knowledge** (Milvus) | 25% | 5 | 1.3 | 7,313 write failures/30m, 2 missing collections, 1 schema mismatch |\n| **Observability** (Prometheus, Loki, Admin) | 20% | 35 | 7.0 | Prometheus 50/54 targets up, Loki working, but Admin MCP fully blocked (all 5 tools) |\n| **Data Layer** (Postgres, Redis) | 20% | 30 | 6.0 | Redis `zremrangebyscore` broken = no rate limiting; Postgres health unverifiable |\n| **Kubernetes / Infra** | 15% | 40 | 6.0 | 4 Prometheus targets persistently down, K8s MCP has no kubeconfig, 0 alerting rules |\n| | | **Total** | **38.3** | |\n\n---\n\n### Top 3 Issues Requiring Immediate Attention\n\n### 1. Milvus Embedding Dimension Mismatch — 7,313 Failed Writes in 30 Minutes\n\nThis is the single highest-volume failure on the platform. The `AzureSDKKnowledgeIngester` generates embeddings via **Amazon Titan Embed v2** at **1,024 dimensions**, but the Milvus collection `chat_conversations_v2` expects **1,536 dimensions**. Every insert is rejected.\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|------:|\n| **Failed writes (30m)** | 7,313 |\n| **Sustained error rate** | ~5 errors/sec (steady-state), spiking to **578/sec** |\n| **Collections affected** | `chat_conversations_v2` (dim mismatch), `azure_sdk_documentation` (field `source` not found) |\n| **Collections missing entirely** | `chat_conversations`, `app_documentation` |\n| **RAG search results returned** | **0** (confirmed in ArtifactService logs) |\n\n**Business impact:** Every user interaction that relies on knowledge retrieval — Azure SDK help, conversation history recall, documentation search — returns **zero results**. The LLM is answering purely from its training data with no platform-specific context.\n\n**Fix:** Either recreate the Milvus collections with `dim=1024` to match Titan Embed v2, or configure the embedding service to output 1,536 dimensions to match the existing schema. The former is faster; the latter preserves any existing data.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Redis Client API Break — Rate Limiting Completely Disabled\n\nThe `ChatAuthService` calls `redis.zremrangebyscore()` on every incoming chat request and gets:\n\n```\n\"redis.zremrangebyscore is not a function\"\n```\n\nThis was observed **3 times in 30 minutes** (once per user session in the window), and the service catches the error and **allows the request through unconditionally**.\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|------:|\n| **Occurrences in 30m** | 3 (1 per chat session start) |\n| **Rate limiting status** | **Completely bypassed** |\n| **Affected service** | `ChatAuthService` in `openagentic-api-6ffdf956b5-6gztf` |\n| **Root cause** | Redis client library upgrade (likely ioredis v4→v5 camelCase rename) |\n\n**Business impact:** Any user or bot can send unlimited requests with zero throttling. This is both a **cost exposure** (uncontrolled Bedrock API spend) and a **security vulnerability** (no abuse protection).\n\n**Fix:** Update the call from `redis.zremrangebyscore()` to `redis.zRemRangeByScore()` (ioredis v5 convention), or pin ioredis to v4.x.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Admin MCP Total Failure — 5 Health Tools Blocked, Postgres Unverifiable\n\nEvery tool in the `oap-admin-mcp` server returns:\n\n```\nInternal error: \"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\"\n```\n\nThis is a Python logging framework bug where a custom handler or formatter sets an attribute named `args` on `LogRecord`, conflicting with the built-in field.\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|------:|\n| **Blocked tools** | `admin_full_system_test`, `postgres_health_check`, `redis_health_check`, `milvus_health_check`, `infrastructure_health_check`, `postgres_raw_query` |\n| **Audits affected** | 3+ consecutive audits (persisting across sessions) |\n| **Postgres vacuum query** | ❌ Could not execute — your `pg_stat_user_tables` query is unrunnable |\n| **Direct consequence** | Database layer health is **completely unobservable** through platform tooling |\n\n**Business impact:** You cannot verify PostgreSQL dead tuple counts, Redis key patterns, Milvus collection health, or run the full system test. Any database-level degradation (bloat, connection exhaustion, index corruption) will go undetected until it causes a user-facing outage.\n\n**Fix:** In the `oap-admin-mcp` Python codebase, find the logging handler or formatter that sets `record.args` and rename the attribute to avoid the collision with Python's built-in `LogRecord.args`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Posture\n\n```mermaid\nquadrantChart\n    title Platform Health Quadrant\n    x-axis Low Severity --> High Severity\n    y-axis Low Volume --> High Volume\n    quadrant-1 Critical - Fix Now\n    quadrant-2 Monitor\n    quadrant-3 Low Priority\n    quadrant-4 Investigate\n    Milvus Dim Mismatch: [0.9, 0.95]\n    Admin MCP Blocked: [0.85, 0.3]\n    Redis Rate Limit: [0.75, 0.2]\n    Missing Collections: [0.7, 0.6]\n    4 Prom Targets Down: [0.4, 0.15]\n    Flowise Unhealthy: [0.3, 0.1]\n```\n\n> [!CAUTION]\n> The platform scores **38/100** not because it's down, but because **every intelligent feature is silently broken**. Users get responses, but with zero RAG context, no rate protection, and no admin visibility into the data layer. This is a \"lights are on but nobody's home\" scenario that will erode trust in platform quality if not addressed within the next deployment cycle."}

